The Venice Film Festival attracts Timothée Chalamet, Zendaya and an epic space adventure. Now it is clear that the hotly anticipated "Dune" will have its world premiere at this autumn's festival. On September 3, it's time, Variety announces.

<a>https://outof.cards/hearthstone/decks/27324-can-take-our-self</a>

Director Denis Villeneuve has put together a fittingly epic cast that includes Oscar Isaac, Javier Bardem, Josh Brolin, Jason Momoa, Charlotte Rampling and the Swedes Stellan Skarsgård and Rebecca Ferguson. "<a>LUCA ITA</a>" is of course based on Frank Herbert's iconic sci-fi novel and has long been something of a dream project for Villeneuve. The ambitious plan is to follow up the film with both a "Dune 2" and a TV series.

&nbsp;

...
<h4 class="engine-dark-box"></h4>
&nbsp;

Standard Flundereeze deck excluding Snowl, Unknown Wind, and the Barrier Statue. Primary win-con hopes to establish Empen + counter trap with protection from either Apex Avian or Solemn.

&nbsp;

Field spell + any level 1 Flunder unopposed results in Empen and the counter trap. Any two level 1 Flunders with the field spell makes it consistent through Ash/Imperm. Without the field spell, the deck is fragile. Sauravis mitigates this to a degree, and can be run as an alternative to the 3x Empen and counter trap.

&nbsp;

Zeus can be summoned if the opponent's turn ends with two level 1 Flunders or one level 1 Flunder and another level 1 in hand. Note that controlling <strong>any</strong> special summoned monsters turns off the counter trap. The extra deck in general exists for Pot of Prosperity but can provide utility if necessary.

&nbsp;

Side deck includes options for going second and the Simorgh lock.
